@*
    CODESNIPPET COMPONENT — Blazor Concept: [Parameter] Properties

    React equivalent: <CodeSnippet code={code} title="C# Code" />
    Angular equivalent: <app-code-snippet [code]="code" [title]="'C# Code'" />

    Key Blazor concepts:
    1. [Parameter] — Like React props or Angular @Input()
       Blazor: [Parameter] public string Code { get; set; }
       React:  function CodeSnippet({ code }: Props)
       Angular: @Input() code: string;

    2. @if — Conditional rendering
       Blazor: @if (Title != null) { <div>@Title</div> }
       React:  {title && <div>{title}</div>}
       Angular: @if (title) { <div>{{title}}</div> }

    3. @ prefix renders C# expressions in HTML (Razor syntax)
       Blazor: <code>@Code</code>
       React:  <code>{code}</code>
       Angular: <code>{{code}}</code>
*@
<div class="code-snippet">
    @if (Title != null)
    {
        <div class="code-title">@Title</div>
    }
    <pre class="code-block"><code>@Code</code></pre>
</div>

@code {
    // [Parameter] makes these properties settable from parent components
    // React equivalent: destructuring props — { code, title }
    // Angular equivalent: @Input() decorator
    [Parameter] public string Code { get; set; } = "";
    [Parameter] public string? Title { get; set; }
}
